==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Retinal
<hw>Ret"i*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
retinoid compound (<chform>C20H28O</chform>), closely related to vitamin
A, which is a component of the visual pigments in the eye. It is also
called <altname>retinaldehyde</altname> and <altname>vitamin A
aldehyde</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retinalite</ent>⟦br⟧
